A PAM module to use a bitcoin address for credentials

Note: this is a work in progress leading up to release 1.0.0

Build
=====
./autogen.sh
./configure --prefix=/usr
make
make install

Install
=======

1. Build and install this package, libpam-bitcoin.
2. Edit /etc/pam.d/login and add the lines from examples/login.diff
3. cp examples/bitcoin.access /etc/
4. Edit /etc/bitcoin.access and include list of allowed addresses/user pairs

Example
=======

$ telnet localhost
Trying 127.0.0.1...
Connected to localhost.
Escape character is '^]'.
Ubuntu 13.10
